<h1 class='property-title'>border-image-width</h1>
<p class='property-description'>The <code>border-image-width</code> CSS property defines the offset to use for dividing the border image in nine parts, the top-left corner, central top edge, top-right-corner, central right edge, bottom-right corner, central bottom edge, bottom-left corner, and central right edge. They represent inward distance from the top, right, bottom and right edges.</p>